## 3. Plan Maintenance

**User Goal:** Schedule maintenance intervention for an asset

### Railnova Flow
**Source:** `railnova-fleet-availability-gantt.png`

![Railnova Gantt](../images/competitive-research/railnova-fleet-availability-gantt.png)

**Steps:**

| Step | Action | UI Element | Result |
|------|--------|------------|--------|
| 1 | Navigate to Fleet Availability | Sidebar → Fleet Availability | Gantt view loads |
| 2 | Find asset in list | Y-axis asset list or search | Asset row visible |
| 3 | Identify available time slot | Grey gaps in timeline | Available window found |
| 4 | Hover for details | Tooltip | See existing interventions |
| 5 | Click to schedule | Click on timeline | Create intervention modal |
| 6 | Fill details | Form inputs | Intervention type, duration |
| 7 | Save | Save button | Intervention appears on Gantt |

**UX Analysis:**

| Heuristic | Score | Evidence |
|-----------|-------|----------|
| Visibility of status | ✅ Good | Gantt shows all commitments |
| User control | ✅ Good | Can click and drag to adjust |
| Error prevention | ⚠️ Medium | Some overlap checking unclear |

**MMS-MFC Gap:**
- Current: MaintenanceGantt exists but vertical orientation
- Missing: Click-to-create intervention

**Recommendation:**
```
CONSIDER: Horizontal Gantt option (industry standard)
ADD: Click on empty space to create intervention
ADD: Drag to adjust duration
ADD: Conflict warning if overlapping
```

