## 4. Allocate Resource

**User Goal:** Assign available train to an uncovered service

### SignatureRail Flow
**Source:** `signaturerail-fleetmanager-video-frame3.png`

![SignatureRail Gantt](../images/competitive-research/signaturerail-fleetmanager-video-frame3.png)

**Steps:**

| Step | Action | UI Element | Result |
|------|--------|------------|--------|
| 1 | Open Fleet Manager | Application launch | Gantt loads |
| 2 | Identify uncovered train | Red/highlighted row | Gap in service visible |
| 3 | Check available resources | Adjacent rows | Find available train |
| 4 | Drag service block | Drag and drop | Service moves to available train |
| 5 | Confirm allocation | Dialog | Allocation saved |

**UX Analysis:**

| Heuristic | Score | Evidence |
|-----------|-------|----------|
| Direct manipulation | ✅ Good | Drag and drop is intuitive |
| Visibility | ✅ Good | See all trains at once |
| Aesthetic design | ❌ Poor | Legacy Windows UI |

**MMS-MFC Gap:**
- Current: Allocation page exists but different paradigm
- Missing: Visual Gantt-based allocation

**Recommendation:**
```
CONSIDER: Gantt-based allocation view
ADD: Drag and drop service blocks
ADD: Highlight uncovered services clearly
ADD: Availability indicator per train
```

